The array doesn&#39;t render because you are using non-numeric indexes on your array. This is described in more detail [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52395924), but basically non-numeric indexes can&#39;t be iterated over so they won&#39;t appear in the output.

A more standard way to handle this would be to use an object instead of an array. Here&#39;s a working version of your component:

```js
Vue.component(&quot;alphabets&quot;, {
  props: [&#39;data&#39;],
  computed: {
    stack() {
      const result = {};
      this.data.forEach(function(element) {
        if (Array.isArray(result[element.artist[0]])) {
          result[element.artist[0]].push(element.artist);
        } else {
          result[element.artist[0]] = [element.artist];
        }
      });
      return result;
    },
  },
  template: `&lt;div&gt;{{ stack }}&lt;/div&gt;`,
});
```

Note this version uses a [computed property](https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/computed.html) instead of modifying the component&#39;s state on `created`.

